<subSubSection pageId="56" pageNumber="57" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="56.[151,1436,1160,1439]" box="[151,571,1160,1187]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,530,1160,1187]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Number of specimens recorded.</emphasis>
13.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="56.[151,1436,1160,1439]" box="[199,1055,1196,1223]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1196,1223]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Distribution.</emphasis>
Europe; also North Africa. 
<collectingCountry box="[663,762,1197,1223]" name="Portugal" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Portugal</collectingCountry>
: three northern provinces.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="56.[151,1436,1160,1439]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,300,1233,1259]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Ecology.</emphasis>
Recorded from three macrohabitat categories in 
<collectingCountry box="[853,951,1233,1259]" name="Portugal" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Portugal</collectingCountry>
, in particular riverbanks and forests; in the latter habitat 
<typeStatus box="[301,352,1269,1295]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">type</typeStatus>
, the species was always collected close to open water (
<emphasis box="[979,1006,1270,1295]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">i.e</emphasis>
., waterfalls, seeps). Like the previous species, in northwestern Europe 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sympycninae" baseAuthorityName="Loew" baseAuthorityYear="1850" box="[525,626,1305,1331]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Syntormon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zelleri">
<emphasis box="[525,626,1305,1331]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">S. zelleri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is mainly distributed at higher altitudes where is mostly found nearby streams in open biotopes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="56.[151,1436,1160,1439]" box="[199,524,1376,1403]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,1376,1403]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Rarity (%).</emphasis>
6.9 (fairly rare).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="56.[151,1436,1160,1439]" box="[199,730,1412,1439]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,386,1412,1439]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Activity period.</emphasis>
March, June–July, September.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
